text: Drosera finlaysoniana is a carnivorous herb found in Australia and south east Asia. More commonly found in the north of Australia. In southern Australian sites it has been recorded at inland areas, in eucalyptus woodlands subject to flooding. Also found in Hainan, Taiwan, the Indo-China region and the Philippines. ==References== Category:Carnivorous plants of Australia Category:Plants described in 1837 finlaysoniana Category:Caryophyllales of Australia Category:Eudicots of Western Australia Category:Flora of South Australia Category:Flora of Queensland Category:Flora of New South Wales Category:Flora of Victoria (Australia) Category:Flora of Asia Category:Flora of the Philippines Category:Flora of Hainan
